abstract: Florida authorities say there is not enough evidence to warrant murder charges in 2010 shooting death of Michelle O'Connell; she suffered gunshot at home of boyfriend Jeremy Banks, who is sheriff's deputy in St John's County; Banks said O'Connell used his weapon to commit suicide, which her family disputed.
lead_paragraph: An investigation ordered by the governor into the shooting death of Michelle O’Connell clears Ms. O’Connell’s sheriff’s deputy boyfriend.

headline.main: No Charges in 2010 Shooting of a Florida Mother
headline.print_headline: No Charges in 2010 Shooting of a Florida Mother
